<br>
So of the 9 DNC presidential candidates, only 4 had actually planned to attend the NAACP convention. And 2 of those 4 happen to be black. <br>
<br>
So despite the fact that black voters overwhelmingly vote for the DNC, roughly 9 out of 10, only 2 of the 7 white Democrat presidential candidates felt the NAACP convention was important enough to attend. ROFL! Now that's what you call taking a group of people for granted!<br>
<br>
